The paper focuses on the analysis of social networks and the spread of information on them, which falls under the scope of social computing (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SOC). The study also involves the extraction and analysis of large datasets, which could be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper discusses the structure of networks and global patterns of information flow, which could be related to the field of system dynamics (cs.SD).
